cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.DC, cs.FL 

This paper deals with the comparison of two classes of typed concurrent processes, specifically focusing on liveness properties such as progress or deadlock freedom. This topic falls under the area of process calculi and concurrency theory, which is typically classified under cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.PL (Programming Languages). The paper also discusses the encoding of session types, which is relevant to the area of software engineering (cs.SE) and distributed computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper introduces a new expressiveness hierarchy for typed processes, which could be of interest to researchers in formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL).
